[docs]    def __init__(self, device=None, external_json=None):
        self.blockname = device
        self.detection = {}
        self.report_before = {}
        self.report_after = {}
        self.data = self.get_data(device)



[docs]    def get_data(self, device):
        detection = self.detection
        report_before = self.report_before
        report_after = self.report_after
        data = {}
        if not detection:
            smart = self._get_smart(device)
            detection['SMART'] = smart
            data.update(smart)
        else:
            if not report_before:
                report = self._get_report(device)
                report_before["generate_report_before"] = report
                data.update(report_before)
            else:
                report = self._get_report(device)
                report_after["generate_report_after"] = report
                config_before = report_before["generate_report_before"]
                config_after = report_after["generate_report_after"]
                data.update(report_after)
                waf = self._WAF(config_before, config_after, device)
                data.update(waf)
                self.report_before = {}

        data['logical_drive'] = device
        data['manufacturer'] = 'HGST'
        data['serial_number'] = ""
        data['type'] = DiskUtils.get_device_type(device)
        data['interface'] = 'nvme'
        return data

[docs]    def validate_rules(self, compare):
        data = {}
        for k, v in compare.items():
            data[k] = v
        criteria_1 = {
            'temperature': 90,
            'media_and_data_integrity_errors': 0,
            'total_uncorrected_write_errors': 0,
            'total_uncorrected_read_errors': 0,
            'total_uncorrected_erase_errors': 0}
        criteria_2 = {'life_gauge': 0, 'available_spare': 10}
        for key, val in data.items():
            for key1, val1 in criteria_1.items():
                for key2, val2 in criteria_2.items():
                    error = "ERROR: %s is %s, higher than threshold \
                        of %s" % (key1, val, val1)
                    threshold_error1 = error
                    threshold_error2 = error
                    if key == key1 and val > val1:
                        raise Exception(threshold_error1)
                    elif key2 == key and val2 == val:
                        raise Exception(threshold_error2)



[docs]    def to_config_dict(self, data):
        return super(HGST, self).to_config_dict(data)


    def _get_report(self, device):
        out = self._get_json("generate-report", device)
        # Example output:
        # {"get-capacity":
        #   {"/dev/nvme0n1":
        #       {"capacity":"1.6TB","num_channels":16}
        #   }}
        decoded = out['results'][0]
        log = {}
        for key, value in decoded.items():
            log[key] = value
        return log

    def _get_smart(self, device):
        out = self._get_json("get-smart", device)
        smart = {}
        for key, value in out.items():
            smart[key] = value
        return smart

    def _get_json(self, option, device):
        dev = device[:5]
        cmd = "/opt/HGST/hdm/bin/hdm --output-format \
            json %s -p /dev/%s" % (option, dev)
        out = AutovalUtils.run_get_output(cmd)
        decoded = json.loads(out)
        return decoded


[docs]    def _WAF(self, config_before, config_after, device):
        """
        HOST and NAND write bytes are captured before and after
        test to determine total logical & physical write bytes.
        NAND total write will then divide to NAND total write
        to calcuate Flash Wrirte Amplification.
        """
        compare = AutovalUtils.compare_configs(config_before, config_after)

        waf = {}
        host_write_before = compare['host_write_blocks'][0]
        host_write_after = compare['host_write_blocks'][1]
        host_delta = (host_write_after - host_write_before)
        waf["host_total_write_blocks"] = host_delta

        nand_write_before = compare['nand_write_blocks'][0]
        nand_write_after = compare['nand_write_blocks'][1]
        nand_delta = (nand_write_after - nand_write_before)
        waf["nand_total_write_blocks"] = nand_delta

        WAF = (nand_delta / host_delta)
        waf["write_Amplification"] = WAF
        return waf
